	(@AbolethAmphibiousId, 'The aboleth can breathe air and water.'),
	(@AbolethMucousCloudId, 'While underwater, the aboleth is surrounded by transformative mucus. A creature that touches the aboleth or that hits it with a melee attack while within 5 feet of it must make a DC 14 Constitution saving throw. On a failure, the creature is diseased for 1d4 hours. The diseased creature can breathe only underwater.'),
